Three Black Crows

    Definition: A bearish continuation/reversal pattern with three long bearish candles, each closing lower than the previous, often after an uptrend.
    Criteria:
        All three candles: Bearish (close < open), with each close < previous close.
        Each candle: Body ≥ 60% of range, minimal shadows.
    What It Tells a Trader:
        Strong Bearish Momentum: Indicates sustained selling pressure, either continuing a downtrend or reversing an uptrend.
        Context-Dependent: Effective at resistance levels or after consolidation.
    How to Trade It:
        Entry: Short at the third candle’s close or on a pullback to the third candle’s open.
        Stop-Loss: Above the first candle’s high (1-2x atr14).
        Take-Profit: Next support (2-3x risk).
        Confirmation: RSI < 50, ADX > 25, high volume_surge_ratio, order_book_imbalance < 0.5.
        Futures Notes: Low leverage, confirm trend strength, check bid_ask_spread.